                <head>Why zines work</head>
                <list>
                    <item>
                        <hi>What is a zine ?</hi>
                        <p>A zine is a booklet made by a transgender anarchist who doesn't have any
                            other options. The Zine is a format that's good at containing
                            information. A zine is a unit, a thing, a piece of information. A zine
                            is, specifically, a <hi>chunk</hi> of information. It is made of + 7
                            smaller chunks of information.</p>
                        <p>A page folded thrice makes for eight portions; six smaller pages and
                            cover : this is the classic format.</p>
                    </item>
                </list>
            </div1>
            <div1 n="2" rendition="#printed">
                <list>
                    <item><hi>WHen Doesn't it Work ?</hi>
                        <p>My last issue was a moment's musing about pet play. People liked it! My
                            previous was about a much more interesting topic I've been researching
                            for a long time, and nobody cared. *<anchor xml:id="footnote1"/></p>
                        <p>Why did one work, and the other didn't ? I think it was the format. I
                            broke the format with the flop : it was a double issue. Double was too
                            much ! Even I got bored in the middle. I should have listened to Miller
                            and his famous laws.</p>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <trailer>
                    * <ptr target="#footnote1"/> <objectName>#89 Puppygirl &amp; Philosopher</objectName> &amp; <objectName>#87 Synagogue Zodiac Mosaic</objectName>
